<https://w3id.org/aief/belongsToFramework> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/aief/hasRequirement> .
<https://w3id.org/aief/mitigatedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/aief/mitigates> .
<https://w3id.org/aief/> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Ontology for multi-framework AI ethics compliance assessment" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Framework> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A governance or regulatory framework defining ethics requirements for AI research." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Requirement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A normative statement derived from a governance framework specifying what a researcher must, may, or must not do." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Tier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Classification of a requirement by its conditionality. Tier 1 requirements are mandatory for all research proposals. Tier 2 requirements are reflective prompts that apply conditionally based on research context." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/EUCharterRight> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A fundamental right protected under the Charter of Fundamental Rights of the European Union (2000/C 364/01)." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Stakeholder> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An individual or organisational role involved in the research ethics assessment process." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Evidence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A document or artefact that demonstrates compliance with an ethics requirement." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/RiskCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A category of harm or risk that an AI system may cause to individuals, groups, or society." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/DataCategory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A classification of personal or research data relevant to ethics assessment, aligned with GDPR data categories." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Mitigation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A technical or organisational measure that reduces the likelihood or severity of an identified risk." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AssessmentProcess> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A formal procedure for evaluating ethics compliance, risk, or impact of a research project or AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ComplianceStatus> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The compliance state of a requirement within a given research project assessment." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/REAMS> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Trinity College Dublin Research Ethics Application Management System. Institutional ethics framework for research approval." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/EUAIAct> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Regulation (EU) 2024/1689 of the European Parliament and of the Council on Artificial Intelligence. FRIA requirements from Article 27." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HorizonEurope> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "European Commission ethics requirements for Horizon Europe funded research projects." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACMConference> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Research ethics and broader impact requirements from ACM, NeurIPS, FAccT, AAAI, and ACL Rolling Review conference submission guidelines." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Obligation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ethics requirement that must be fulfilled. Aligned with ODRL Duty." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Obligation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ethics requirement specifying an action that must be performed. Aligned with ODRL Duty." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Prohibition> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ethics requirement that forbids a specific action. Aligned with ODRL Prohibition." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Prohibition> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ethics requirement specifying an action that is forbidden. Aligned with ODRL Prohibition." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Permission> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ethics requirement that permits a specific action under defined conditions. Aligned with ODRL Permission." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Permission> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An ethics requirement specifying an action that is permitted under defined conditions. Aligned with ODRL Permission." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Tier1_Mandatory> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Requirements that apply to all research proposals regardless of context. Failure to comply blocks ethics approval." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Tier2_Reflective> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Requirements that apply conditionally based on research context. Researchers must reflect on whether these apply to their specific project." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Title1_Dignity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "EU Charter of Fundamental Rights Title I covering Articles 1–5 on human dignity." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art1_HumanDignity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Human dignity is inviolable. It must be respected and protected." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art2_RightToLife> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right to life." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art3_RightToIntegrity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right to respect for his or her physical and mental integrity." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art5_ProhibitionOfSlavery> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "No one shall be held in slavery or servitude." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Title2_Freedoms> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "EU Charter Title II covering Articles 6–19 on freedoms." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art6_RightToLiberty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right to liberty and security of person." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art7_PrivateLife> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right to respect for his or her private and family life, home and communications." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art8_DataProtection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right to the protection of personal data concerning him or her." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art10_FreedomOfThought> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right to freedom of thought, conscience and religion." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art11_FreedomOfExpression> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right to freedom of expression. This right shall include freedom to hold opinions and to receive and impart information and ideas without interference by public authority." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art16_FreedomToConductBusiness> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The freedom to conduct a business in accordance with Union law and national laws and practices is recognised." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Title3_Equality> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "EU Charter Title III covering Articles 20–26 on equality." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art20_EqualityBeforeLaw> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone is equal before the law." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art21_NonDiscrimination> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Any discrimination based on any ground such as sex, race, colour, ethnic or social origin, genetic features, language, religion or belief, political or any other opinion, membership of a national minority, property, birth, disability, age or sexual orientation shall be prohibited." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art22_CulturalDiversity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Union shall respect cultural, religious and linguistic diversity." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art23_GenderEquality> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Equality between women and men must be ensured in all areas, including employment, work and pay." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art24_RightsOfChild> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Children shall have the right to such protection and care as is necessary for their well-being." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art25_RightsOfElderly> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Union recognises and respects the rights of the elderly to lead a life of dignity and independence." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art26_DisabilityIntegration> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The Union recognises and respects the right of persons with disabilities to benefit from measures designed to ensure their independence, social and occupational integration and participation in the life of the community." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Title4_Solidarity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "EU Charter Title IV covering Articles 27–38 on solidarity and social rights." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art31_FairWorkingConditions> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Every worker has the right to working conditions which respect his or her health, safety and dignity." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art35_HealthCare> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone has the right of access to preventive health care and the right to benefit from medical treatment under the conditions established by national laws and practices." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art37_EnvironmentalProtection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A high level of environmental protection and the improvement of the quality of the environment must be integrated into the policies of the Union." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Title5_CitizensRights> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "EU Charter Title V covering Articles 39–46 on citizens' rights." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art38_ConsumerProtection> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Union policies shall ensure a high level of consumer protection." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art41_GoodAdministration> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Every person has the right to have his or her affairs handled impartially, fairly and within a reasonable time by the institutions and bodies of the Union." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Title6_Justice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "EU Charter Title VI covering Articles 47–50 on justice." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art47_RightToEffectiveRemedy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone whose rights and freedoms guaranteed by the law of the Union are violated has the right to an effective remedy before a tribunal." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Certificate> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A formal certificate demonstrating completion of a required training or qualification." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ConsentForm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A document through which research participants provide informed consent to participate." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/DataProtectionPolicy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An organisational policy documenting how personal data is collected, stored, and processed in compliance with GDPR." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/RiskAssessmentReport> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A document identifying and evaluating potential harms arising from a research project or AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/BiasAssessmentReport> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A document evaluating the presence and extent of bias in an AI system's training data or outputs." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/DPIA> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A systematic assessment of the privacy risks posed by a data processing activity, required under GDPR Article 35." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/FRIA> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An assessment evaluating the impact of an AI system on fundamental rights, as referenced in EU AI Act Article 27." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ModelCard> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A structured document providing transparency about an AI model's intended uses, performance characteristics, and limitations." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/DataSheet> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A structured document describing the composition, collection process, and intended uses of a dataset." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/EthicsApproval> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A formal decision by an ethics committee approving a research project to proceed." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/PhysicalHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of bodily injury, death, or physical safety compromise caused by an AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/PsychologicalHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of mental distress, manipulation, coercion, or emotional damage caused by an AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/FinancialHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of economic loss, fraudulent debt, or material deprivation caused by an AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ReputationalHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of damage to an individual's or organisation's reputation through AI-generated outputs or decisions." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/PrivacyBreach> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of unauthorised collection, processing, or disclosure of personal data by an AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Discrimination> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of unfair differential treatment of individuals or groups based on protected characteristics by an AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/EnvironmentalHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of negative environmental impact including carbon footprint, resource consumption, or ecological damage from AI systems." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/DualUseMisuse> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk that research or AI outputs intended for beneficial purposes are repurposed for harmful applications." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/FunctionCreep> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk that an AI system is used beyond its originally defined and ethically approved purpose." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/WorkplaceSafetyRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of harm to workers arising from AI system deployment in occupational settings." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/DemocraticProcessHarm> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk of undermining democratic institutions, electoral processes, or civic participation through AI systems." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AddictionRisk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk that AI system design exploits psychological vulnerabilities to create compulsive usage patterns." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/EthicsSelfAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A researcher-completed assessment of the ethical implications of a proposed research project." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/RiskAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A formal process for identifying, analysing, and evaluating risks posed by a research project or AI system." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/BiasAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A systematic evaluation of bias in AI training data, model outputs, or decision processes." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/FRIAProcedure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A structured procedure for assessing AI system impacts on fundamental rights, aligned with EU AI Act Article 27." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/DPIAProcedure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A structured procedure for assessing data protection risks under GDPR Article 35." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/EnvironmentalImpactAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A procedure for evaluating the environmental consequences of a research project or AI system deployment." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Compliant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The requirement is fully satisfied by the research project." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/NonCompliant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The requirement is not satisfied and remediation is required before ethics approval." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/PartiallyCompliant> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The requirement is partially satisfied but gaps remain that must be addressed." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/NotApplicable> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The requirement does not apply to this research project given its specific context and scope." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Incident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A documented real-world event in which an AI system caused or contributed to harm, rights violations, or ethical failures." .
<https://w3id.org/aief/Art48_PresumptionOfInnocence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Everyone who has been charged shall be presumed innocent until proved guilty according to law." .
