<https://w3id.org/aief/R001> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Applicant must be identified with name, staff/student number, email, school/department" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R005> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Applicant must have completed Data Protection Training within last 24 months" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R010> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Assess whether research could have detrimental legal, economic or social consequences for participants" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R019> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Will consent be obtained from participants (or proxy/guardian)?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R027> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Describe general characteristics of target population (vulnerability status, children, staff/students)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R042> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "How will consent be obtained and by whom?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R054> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Identify risks to participants: inconvenience, physical, emotional, reputational, financial, privacy, intrusive, harmful" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R071> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Describe security measures for data access, storage, transfer" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R074> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "For each processing risk: list risk, severity/impact, likelihood, mitigation actions" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R085> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered anti-discrimination and bias implications of your AI/technology research?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R002> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Applicant must confirm role on project (PI / Non-PI / Other)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R003> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Applicant must have read and understood Trinity Policy on Good Research Practice" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R004> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Applicant must have completed Research Integrity Training Module" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R006> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "All Trinity collaborators must be listed with role, name, email, school" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R007> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "All non-Trinity collaborators must be listed with role, name, affiliation, country" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R008> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Project title, data collection start/end dates, project end date must be specified" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R009> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify whether project involves humans/their data OR animals" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R011> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Declare intentions of study: deception, illegal activity, intrusive/harmful topics, military role, dual purpose" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R012> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "State research aims, objectives, research question or hypothesis (100 words)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R013> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Lay summary including background, rationale, research approach, study design (250 words)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R014> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Identify all countries where data is collected or processed" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R015> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify what project involves: human participants/data only, biological samples (various levels)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R016> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Declare whether project is funded" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R017> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Declare if study is phased" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R018> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify data sources: primary only, secondary only, or both" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R020> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Will payment be made to participants? Standard gratuity vs excess" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R021> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Is the project Health Research under HRR 2018?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R022> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Does the project require a Consent Declaration under HRR?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R023> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Are you processing any personal data for your research project?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R024> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Are you processing any pseudonymised (coded) data?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R025> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Are you processing personal data for participant recruitment?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R026> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "If processing recruitment data: outline storage, confidentiality, destruction plan" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R028> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "List inclusion/exclusion criteria for participant selection" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R029> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Name each data collection site/source" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R030> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "For each site: licence, permission, or ethics approval status" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R031> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Was a DPIA required at each site/source?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R032> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Outline data collection methods" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R033> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify if methods are exclusively low-risk (quality assurance, anonymous surveys, public observation, audits, public domain data)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R034> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Does the project include an intervention?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R035> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Approximate target population size and proposed sample size" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R036> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Justification for sample size" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R037> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Outline method of analysis (100 words)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R038> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Outline sampling method" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R039> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Describe time commitment of participants" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R040> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Will research use a gatekeeper? If yes: role, position, dependent relationship?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R041> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Step-by-step description of participant recruitment process" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R043> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Do participants require support to give consent?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R044> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Is assent required from participants due to vulnerability?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R045> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Is Garda vetting required?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R046> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Time interval between giving information and securing consent (min 7 days recommended)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R047> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "How will participants be informed about use of their personal data?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R048> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "How can participants withdraw consent and/or their data?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R049> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify data collection setting(s)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R050> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Identify risks to researcher: intrusive topic, emotional, physical, other, none" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R051> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "For each researcher risk: estimate impact, likelihood, detail mitigation" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R052> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Identify risks to site, environment, or society" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R053> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Declare if dependent relationship exists between researcher and participants" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R055> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Could participants reveal legally disclosable information (child protection, malpractice)?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R056> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Outline direct benefits of participation" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R057> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Declare any conflict of interest from PI or collaborators" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R058> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "RPAMS number if applicable" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R059> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "List all sources of funding with type (industrial, state, philanthropic, other)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R060> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Funder-specific requirements or obligations for ethics committee attention" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R061> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Will results be used/disclosed for commercial purposes?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R062> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Conflict of interest from funding or commercialisation" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R063> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "All Trinity researchers completed GDPR training?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R064> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "All Trinity staff/students familiar with Personal Data Breach Procedural Guidelines?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R065> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "What is Trinity's role: Controller, Joint Controller, or Processor?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R066> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Number of participants whose personal data is processed (≥100 or <100)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R067> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "List all types of personal data processed (including special category)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R068> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Does project involve special category data or criminal conviction data?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R069> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Is personal data shared within Trinity (outside research team)?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R070> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Is personal data shared with third parties outside Trinity?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R072> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Are personal data transferred outside UK/EEA?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R073> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Detail how long personal data retained in identifiable/coded format" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R075> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "All required attachments uploaded (consent forms, certificates, PIL, recruitment material, methods instruments, DPO letter)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R076> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Participant Information Leaflet appropriate for target audience (plain English, accessible format)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R077> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Applicant declaration: accuracy, compliance with Good Research Practice, GDPR, HRR, TCD policies" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R078> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "PI declaration and approval (if applicant ≠ PI)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R079> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Supervisor declaration and approval (all student applications)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R080> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether research could be misdirected for dual purpose / harm?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R081> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether your recruitment could unintentionally include vulnerable participants?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R082> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered the worst-case scenario for each identified risk?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R083> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered indirect identifiability from participant profiles in small populations?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R084> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether anonymised data could be re-identified?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R086> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered the impact on personal autonomy of the technology being researched?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/R087> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered environmental impact of compute-intensive AI research?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI001> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Assess whether organisation is obligated to conduct a FRIA (deployer of high-risk AI system)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI002> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Record necessity status: FRIA Required or FRIA Not Required" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI003> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Record when FRIA was created, modified, submitted, accepted" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI004> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Record who conducted the FRIA (organisation, personnel, contributors)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI005> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Record identifier/version of FRIA — must be regularly updated" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI006> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Record conformance to any codes of conduct" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI007> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Describe deployer's processes in which the AI system will be used" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI008> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "State the intended purpose of the AI system" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI009> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify the period of time and frequency the AI system is intended to be used" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI010> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Describe the intended use — specific deployment scenarios distinct from intended purpose" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI011> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Identify categories of natural persons and groups likely to be affected by the AI system in the specific context" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI012> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Assess the likelihood that those persons/groups will be affected" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI013> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Identify consequences and impacts on affected persons/groups" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI014> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Identify specific risks of harm to fundamental rights" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI015> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Describe human oversight measures in place" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI016> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify what humans can and cannot do — ability to correct outputs, ability to opt out, override capability" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI017> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Reference instructions for use provided by the AI system provider" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI018> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Specify measures to be taken if risks materialise — internal governance arrangements and complaint mechanisms" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI019> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "If relying on a previously conducted FRIA, document which prior FRIA is being reused and what has changed" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI020> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "If a DPIA already exists under GDPR, document how it complements the FRIA — what it covers and what gaps remain" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI021> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Determine FRIA outcome status: Unacceptable Risk / High Residual Risk / Risks Acceptable / Risks Mitigated" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI022> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "For each affected fundamental right, state whether there is an impact and its severity" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI023> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "For granular impacts (e.g. discrimination based on sex, race, gender under Art 21), specify the category of impact" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI024> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Assess whether notification to market surveillance authority is required or exempt under Art 46-1" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI025> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "If required: notify market surveillance authority of FRIA results" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI026> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Complete the FRIA questionnaire template provided by the AI Office" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI027> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Document whether an automated tool was used to support the FRIA process" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI028> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether the same AI system with one intended purpose could have different intended uses causing different rights impacts?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI029> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether pseudonymised or anonymised data could still lead to identification of affected individuals?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/AI030> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you assessed impact at the granular level — not just non-discrimination but which specific grounds (sex, race, disability, age)?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE001> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system must not deprive end-users or affected persons of ability to make decisions about their own lives or remove basic freedoms" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE002> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system must not autonomously make decisions about fundamental personal, economic, social or political issues normally decided by humans, without human oversight and redress" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE003> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system must not subordinate, coerce, deceive, manipulate, objectify or dehumanize end-users or affected persons" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE004> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system must not purposely stimulate attachment or addiction" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE005> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system should give operators and end-users ability to control, direct and intervene in basic operations" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE006> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "End-users and affected persons must receive comprehensible information about the AI logic, significance and envisaged consequences" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE007> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system must process personal data lawfully, fairly and transparently" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE008> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Data minimisation and data protection by design and by default must be integrated" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE009> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Appropriate technical and organisational measures must be in place to safeguard rights of data subjects (anonymisation, pseudonymisation, encryption, aggregation)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE010> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Strong security measures must prevent data breaches and leakages" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE011> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Data must be acquired, stored and used in a manner auditable by humans" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE012> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Research proposal must specify steps to ensure data about people is representative of target population and reflects diversity or is sufficiently neutral" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE013> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Document how bias in input data and algorithmic design will be identified and avoided" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE014> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system should be designed for universal accessibility — usable by end-users with different abilities" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE015> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Possible negative social impacts on certain groups must be mitigated, including impacts beyond algorithmic bias" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE016> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Methods to identify and mitigate negative social impacts in medium and longer term must be documented in proposal" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE017> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system must not unduly or unfairly reduce psychological and emotional well-being of end-users and stakeholders" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE018> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI development must be mindful of environmental sustainability — document environmental impact and mitigation steps" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE019> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI systems in media, communications, politics, social analytics must be assessed for potential to negatively impact democratic processes and social relations" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE020> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI and robotics systems must not reduce safety in the workplace" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE021> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "It must be made clear to end-users they are interacting with an AI system" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE022> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Purpose, capabilities, limitations, benefits and risks of AI system must be openly communicated to end-users and stakeholders" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE023> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Traceability measures must be considered for the AI system's entire lifecycle" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE024> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Research proposal should explain how decisions made by system will be explainable to users, including reasons for decisions" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE025> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Development processes must keep records of all relevant decisions regarding ethical compliance" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE026> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Document how ethically and socially undesirable effects will be detected, stopped and prevented from reoccurring" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE027> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "AI system must allow for human oversight and control over decision cycles and operation, unless compelling justification provided" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE028> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Research proposal should include evaluation of possible ethics risks including risk assessment procedures and post-deployment mitigation" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE029> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider how end-users, data subjects and third parties can report complaints, ethical concerns or adverse events" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE030> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "All AI systems should be auditable by independent third parties — system should generate human-accessible logs" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE031> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Ensure processing of personal data complies with GDPR — prepare specific data protection policy" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE032> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Input, training and output data must all be analysed for bias — verify data accounts for diversity in gender, race, age, sexual orientation, national origin, religion, health, disability" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE033> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Analyse training data for relevance and representativeness — undertake formal bias assessment" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE034> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Ensure ability to go back to each state the system has been in to determine training data used at any point" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE035> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "If creating inferred personal data or aggregating datasets, new data must receive same protection level as original data" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE036> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Ensure no new personal data collected or created during development or use unless necessary" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE037> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Check for algorithmic bias during detailed development phase using methods such as counterfactual evaluation" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE038> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Ensure interface design honours universal accessibility principles" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE039> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Establish traceability and accountability measures covering: design methods, testing methods, system outcomes, and alternative decision scenarios" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE040> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Code must be documented and explained within software and ancillary documentation" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE041> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Use formal methodologies for explainability where possible (XAI, Transparency by Design, Model Cards)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE042> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Test whether users understand they are interacting with non-human agent" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE043> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Ensure audit controls check performance and record decisions about system purpose and functioning" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE044> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Communicate system capabilities and limitations to stakeholders in clear, understandable and proactive manner" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE045> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Establish processes to obtain user feedback and mechanisms to adapt system in response" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE046> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Establish and implement plans supporting operational compliance with ethical requirements" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE047> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Update data, access, security and risk management policies to account for ethical requirements" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE048> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Establish monitoring goals and metrics for ethics compliance — periodically monitor and improve" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE049> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Ensure AI stakeholders, users and subjects have ethical complaint communication channels" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE050> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether your AI system could be misused or diverted from its original purpose (function creep)?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE051> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered the system's impact on social cohesion and democratic processes?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/HE052> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you assessed the environmental footprint of your AI system's compute and supply chain?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM001> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Research must contribute to society and human well-being — discuss how applications may harm individuals, groups or society and ways to mitigate such harms" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM002> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Avoid harm — consider how data, code or other outcomes of research may cause harm" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM003> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Be fair and take action not to discriminate — consider and ameliorate biases the approach may perpetuate" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM004> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider and ameliorate biases in data and biased code/model outputs" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM005> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Respect intellectual property and data/code ownership — cite creators of artefacts used and use them as intended (respect licences)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM006> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Respect privacy — obtain informed consent where required and protect personally identifiable information" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM007> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Give comprehensive evaluation of systems and their impacts including analysis of possible risks of applications" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM008> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider possible risks and impacts of the research approach itself (not just applications)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM009> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Access computing and communication resources only when authorised or compelled by public good" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM010> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Design and implement systems that are robustly and usably secure — especially systems close to production deployment" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM011> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Manage personnel and resources to enhance quality of working life — consider how participation of annotators/crowdworkers may cause benefits or harms" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM012> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider and ameliorate negative impacts of approach on political, social or natural environment" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM013> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Discuss dual use potential — ways research could be misused and mitigations" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM014> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "All human research subjects or participants must receive appropriate compensation — respect minimum hourly rate in region where work is carried out" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM015> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Research involving human participants must follow existing institutional protocols (IRB or equivalent) — if no formal process exists, undergo equivalent informal ethics review" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM016> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Datasets should minimise exposure of personally identifiable information unless informed consent is provided" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM017> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Datasets with real data of real people must have explicit consent of participants, or explain why consent was not obtained" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM018> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Authors must confirm datasets are still available for use — deprecated datasets should not be used except for audit or critical assessment" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM019> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Respect terms of datasets with defined licences (CC 4.0, MIT etc)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM020> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Assess and communicate degree to which datasets are representative of intended population — claims of diverse representation must be substantiated" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM021> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider whether technology can be used to harm, injure or kill people through direct application, side effects or misuse" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM022> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider risk that applications could open security vulnerabilities or cause serious accidents — recommend or implement protections" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM023> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider whether technology can be used to discriminate, exclude or negatively impact people including healthcare, education or credit access" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM024> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consult local laws before collecting or analysing bulk surveillance data — surveillance must not predict protected categories or endanger individual well-being" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM025> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Communicate whether approach could facilitate deceptive interactions causing harm (theft, fraud, harassment), impersonate public figures, influence political processes, or promote hate speech" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM026> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Consider whether research negatively impacts environment — fossil fuel extraction, consumption, greenhouse gas production" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM027> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Research must not build upon or facilitate illegal activity — strongly discourage work that denies rights to privacy, speech, health, liberty, security, legal personhood, freedom of conscience/religion" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM028> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Inspect suspected biases or limitations in models/datasets — ascertain whether they encode bias against gender, race, sexuality or other protected characteristics" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM029> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Provide data and model documentation via structured templates (Model Cards, Datasheets for Datasets)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM030> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Provide licences for released data or models including intended use and limitations" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM031> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Use privacy protocols, encryption and anonymisation to reduce risk of data leakage — stronger measures for sensitive data" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM032> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "High-risk models must be released with safeguards for controlled use (e.g. code of conduct for access)" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM033> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Make accessible all information required to understand research artefacts (code, environment, weights, hyperparameters) to enable external scrutiny" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM034> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Disclose information sufficient for reproduction of results" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM035> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Ensure adequate awareness of regional legal requirements — additional justification required where compliance could not be met due to human rights issues" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM036> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether your NLP/ML system could out, profile or endanger vulnerable individuals?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM037> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered whether crowdworkers/annotators were paid a local living minimum wage and treated fairly?" .
<https://w3id.org/aief/ACM038> <https://w3id.org/aief/requirementText> "Have you considered the carbon footprint of training and deploying your model?" .
